owever%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20one%20state%20has%20been%20running%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eprogram%20that%20some%20researchers%20say%20offers%20similar%20benefits%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-ubi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniversal%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20recurring%20payments%20to%20individuals%20without%20the%20need%20for%20pre-qualification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alaska%20Permanent%20Fund%20distributes%20money%20to%20the%20state's%20residents%20as%20annual%20dividends.%20The%20amount%20of%20the%20dividend%20payments%20varies%20each%20year%20as%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20state's%20annual%20oil%20revenue.%20For%202023%2C%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20Dividend%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpfd.alaska.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%2C312%20per%20person%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20all%20residents%20regardless%20of%20socioeconomic%20status%2C%20down%20from%20%243%2C284%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlaskans%20spend%20significantly%20more%20on%20goods%20like%20clothing%2C%20cleaning%20products%2C%20and%20food%20in%20the%20month%20they%20receive%20the%20payments%2C%20scholarly%20reports%20show.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20fund%20helped%20reduce%20poverty%2C%20improve%20labor%20market%20outcomes%2C%20better%20residents'%20health%2C%20increase%20the%20state's%20fertility%20rate%2C%20and%20improve%20access%20to%20clean%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20results%20echo%20the%20findings%20of%20much%20shorter%20guaranteed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-states-cities-have-guaranteed-basic-income-programs-low-income-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebasic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20pilots%20that%20distribute%20mainly%20%24500%20to%20%241%2C000%20monthly%20to%20Americans.%20Most%20pilots%20cater%20to%20financially%20vulnerable%20Americans%20in%20demographics%20such%20as%20parents%2C%20foster%20youth%2C%20or%20particular%20racial%20identities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20Dividend%20is%20not%20a%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20as%20the%20dividend%20is%20paid%20out%20once%20a%20year%2C%20is%20not%20funded%20by%20taxes%2C%20and%20is%20not%20enough%20money%20to%20live%20on%20each%20year.%20The%20fund%20also%20differs%20from%20basic-income%20pilots%20that%20cater%20only%20to%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20the%20population%2C%20meaning%20findings%20from%20Alaska%20aren't%20easily%20transferable%20to%20these%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227a46091-8844-4782-a9a2-1860c1e87a4a%5C%22%3EHow%20does%20the%20Alaska%20Permanent%20Fund%20dividend%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201976%2C%20Alaska's%20residents%20voted%20to%20allocate%20at%20least%2025%25%20of%20the%20state's%20annual%20oil%20revenue%20to%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20so%20future%20generations%20could%20benefit%20when%20oil%20is%20less%20prevalent%20in%20the%20economy.%20This%20came%20after%20residents%20expressed%20frustrations%20over%20how%20the%20state%20legislature%20spent%20its%20%24900%20million%20bonus%20from%20oil%20field%20leases.%20The%20initial%20deposit%20into%20the%20fund%20was%20%24734%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fund%20was%20initially%20established%20with%20revenue%20from%20mineral%20extraction%2C%20primarily%20oil%2C%20but%20within%20a%20few%20years%20after%20its%20initiation%2C%20its%20primary%20source%20of%20revenue%20is%20investment%20returns%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sarah%20Cowan%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Cash%20Transfer%20Lab%2C%20which%20conducts%20and%20facilitates%20cash%20transfer%20research%20on%20initiatives%20like%20basic%20income.%20%26quot%3BIt%20diversifies%20the%20Alaskan%20economy%20because%2C%20at%20this%20juncture%2C%20the%20revenue%20from%20this%20fund%20primarily%20does%20not%20come%20from%20oil.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResidents%20who%20lived%20in%20Alaska%20during%20the%20entire%20previous%20year%20are%20eligible%20for%20the%20current%20year's%20dividends.%20And%20Alaskans%20are%20expected%20to%20receive%20their%202024%20PFD%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20June%2030%2C%20the%20fund's%20value%20was%20%2480.3%20billion.%20The%20fund%20is%20divided%20into%20principal%20and%20earnings%20reserve%20parts%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20which%20is%20distributed%20as%20dividends%20to%20applicants.%20The%20principal%20part%20is%20not%20for%20spending%20and%20grows%20from%20royalties%2C%20capital%20gains%2C%20and%20inflation-proofing%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrett%20Watson%2C%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Research%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alaska%20Anchorage%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20money%20goes%20a%20long%20way%20for%20families.%20He%20added%20the%20dividends%20represent%20about%208%25%20of%20total%20annual%20household%20income%20for%20the%20median%20household%20in%20Alaska.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20the%20regular%20workings%20of%20an%20economy%2C%20the%20way%20we%20distribute%20the%20PFD%20in%20Alaska%20is%20all%20the%20cash%20gets%20direct%20deposited%20into%20bank%20accounts%20basically%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20so%20that's%20%241%20billion%20to%20%242%20billion%20every%20year%20basically%20in%20one%20fell%20keyboard%20stroke%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20skyline%20of%20Anchorage%2C%20Alaska%20with%20mountains%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66391aa5b8f515beaf11ea73%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlaskans%20are%20expected%20to%20receive%20their%202024%20PFD%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EJacob%20Boomsma%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f66f7bad-7605-4085-85c6-c3454465d4d1%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20fund%20helps%20residents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiseralaska.org%2Fstatic%2Flegacy_publication_links%2F2016_12-PFDandPoverty-Summary.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeated%20finding%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades%20is%20that%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20Dividend%20reduced%20poverty%20rates%20in%20Alaska.%20A%20paper%20published%20in%20May%20in%20the%20quarterly%20peer-reviewed%20publication%20Poverty%20%26amp%3B%20Public%20Policy%20found%20using%20Census%20data%20that%20from%201990%20to%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets-eu.researchsquare.com%2Ffiles%2Frs-2444526%2Fv1%2F90746b46-ec6e-4e3f-b596-e67c0c3df311.pdf%3Fc%3D1718345765%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoverty%20rates%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202.1%20to%20as%20much%20as%204.2%20percentage%20points%20%E2%80%94%20and%20brought%20the%20poverty%20rate%20for%20Indigenous%20Alaskans%20in%20rural%20areas%20to%2022%25%20from%2028%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20Native%20Alaskans%20choose%20to%20forego%20wage%20and%20salary%20occupation%20to%20pursue%20purely%20traditional%20or%20subsistence%20lifestyles%2C%20but%20having%20access%20to%20some%20cash%20is%20pretty%20essential%20to%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20basic%20provisions%2C%20to%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20hunting%20or%20fishing%20equipment%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%20of%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20Dividend%20have%20somewhat%20weakened%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20as%20the%20dividends%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%20have%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20basic%20income%20are%20hotly%20debated%2C%20but%20critics%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-opposition-discriminatory-universal-basic-income-argument-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20argued%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20giving%20people%20money%20with%20no%20strings%20attached%20could%20limit%20the%20size%20of%20the%20workforce.%20However%2C%20a%20paper%20in%20the%20American%20Economic%20Journal%3A%20Economic%20Policy%20published%20in%202018%20determined%20that%20the%20Permanent%20Fund%20Dividend%20had%20no%20significant%20impact%20on%20employment%20rates%20and%20increased%20the%20frequency%20of%20part-time%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20paper%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Policy%20Analysis%20and%20Management%20published%20in%202022%20found%20that%20a%20%241%2C000%20increase%20in%20the%20PFD%20led%20to%20a%201.7%25%20greater%20probability%20of%20employment%20for%20men.%20However%2C%20for%20women%2C%20employment%20was%20reduced%20by%204%25%2C%20or%201.25%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20though%20this%20decline%20was%20concentrated%20among%20younger%20women%20with%20lower%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increased%20level%20of%20employment%20among%20male%20workers%20may%20be%20evidence%20of%20a%20positive%20labor%20demand%20response%20due%20to%20increased%20demand%20for%20goods%20and%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Andrew%20Bibler%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nevada%2C%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20who%20co-authored%20the%20paper.%20%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20PFD%20could%20create%20job%20opportunities%20for%20some%20workers.%20This%20can%20offset%20the%20negative%20labor%20supply%20response%2C%20which%20is%20a%20common%20criticism%20of%20cash%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dividends%20also%20increased%20fertility%20for%20women%20ages%2020%20to%2044%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1570677X23001156%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20year%20in%20Economics%20%26amp%3B%20Human%20Biology.%20The%20authors%20determined%20that%20a%20few%20years%20after%20the%20first%20payment%2C%20fertility%20increased%20annually%20by%2011.3%20births%20per%201%2C000%20women%2C%20with%20the%20greatest%20percentage%20increase%20in%20those%20aged%2034%20to%2044.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20using%20PFD%20data%2C%20a%20paper%20in%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20published%20last%20year%20determined%20that%20an%20additional%20%241%2C000%20distributed%20to%20families%20early%20in%20a%20child's%20life%20lowers%20the%20chance%20of%20neglect%20and%20child%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20that%20dividends%20also%20improve%20health%20and%20well-being%20outcomes%20for%20families.%20An%20Institute%20of%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Research%2C%20University%20of%20Alaska%20Anchorage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarworks.alaska.edu%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F11122%2F10581%2F2019_05_20-EffectsOfAKPFD.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26isAllowed%3Dy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202019%20outlining%20the%20findings%20of%20past%20research%20about%20the%20program%20shows%20that%20the%20PFD%20has%20had%20significant%20health%20benefits%2C%20such%20as%20reductions%20in%20obesity%20and%20modestly%20positive%20effects%20on%20birth%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.mit.edu%2Frest%2Farticle-abstract%2F102%2F4%2F678%2F96772%2FUniversal-Cash-and-Crime%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproperty%20crime%20fell%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%208%25%20in%20the%20weeks%20after%20payments%2C%20substance-abuse%20incidents%20rose%20by%2010%25%20four%20weeks%20after%2C%20according%20to%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20The%20Review%20of%20Economics%20and%20Statistics%20in%202020%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Overall%2C%20the%20payments%20only%20slightly%20impacted%20criminal%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Watson%20is%20working%20on%20a%20paper%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20show%20that%20people%20from%20various%20backgrounds%20and%20politics%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20move%20to%20another%20state%20if%20they%20received%20dividends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatson%20noted%20that%20lower-income%20residents%20often%20spend%20their%20dividends%20on%20household%20expenditures%2C%20though%20he%20added%20middle-%20and%20higher-income%20households%20%26quot%3Bdisproportionately%26quot%3B%20spend%20their%20checks%20on%20their%20kids%2C%20from%20school%20supplies%20to%20college%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20all%20dividend%20effects%20are%20positive.%20Income%20inequality%20in%20the%20state%20has%20grown%20in%20the%20short%20and%20long%20run%2C%20according%20to%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20Energy%20Economics%20in%202017.%20The%20authors%20suggest%20that%20higher-income%20groups%20may%20save%20and%20invest%20more%2C%20while%20lower-income%20groups%20may%20spend%20more%20on%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20poorly%20targeted%20program%20from%20a%20distributional%20perspective%2C%20but%20that%20kind%20of%20trades%20off%20against%20the%20lack%20of%20stigma%20associated%20with%20targeting%20this%20program%20at%20a%20particular%20subgroup%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223409%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20of%20the%20harbor%20with%20mountains%20in%20the%20background%20in%20Whittier%2C%20Alaska.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6585d2e01c5c7b8c9a0b9775%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResidents%20who%20lived%20in%20Alaska%20during%20the%20entire%20previous%20year%20are%20eligible%20for%20the%20current%20year's%20dividends.%3Cp%3Eannhfhung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5b39812-2607-4da9-a307-0451fc694ee4%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20fund%20started%20and%20changed%20over%20the%20years%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlaska's%20governor%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Jay%20Hammond%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cgdev.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Farchive%2Fdoc%2Fbooks%2FGovernorsSolution%2FCh2_GovernorsSolution.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20an%20unpublished%20manuscript%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20he%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Btransform%20oil%20wells%20pumping%20oil%20for%20a%20finite%20period%20into%20money%20wells%20pumping%20money%20for%20infinity.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Bill%20Walker%2C%20Alaska's%20governor%20from%202014%20to%202018%2C%20cut%20the%20dividend's%20value%20roughly%20in%20half%20amid%20falling%20oil%20prices.%20This%20pattern%20of%20cutting%20dividends%20continued%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVox%20reported%20how%20current%20Gov.%20Mike%20Dunleavy%20promised%20residents%20up%20to%20%246%2C700%20annually%20to%20compensate%20for%20this%20lost%20income%2C%20though%20payments%20have%20remained%20well%20below%20this.%20Dunleavy%20has%20advocated%20for%20higher%20dividends%20recently%20%E2%80%94%20proposing%20a%20%243%2C700%20annual%20dividend%20in%202022%20as%20oil%20revenues%20skyrocketed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatson%20said%20that%20though%20the%20state%20continues%20to%20prioritize%20the%20dividends%2C%20it%20competes%20against%20other%20state%20government%20spending%20for%20education%2C%20Medicaid%2C%20and%20other%20social%20services%20as%20oil%20revenue%20falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Alaska%2C%20many%20other%20US%20states%20have%20basic%20income%20programs.%20Some%20are%20geared%20toward%20specific%20groups%2C%20like%20new%20parents%20and%20pregnant%20people.%20Meanwhile%2C%20other%20countries%20have%20experimented%20with%20basic%20income%2C%20including%20Canada%2C%20Kenya%2C%20and%20Ireland.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatson%20said%20the%20program%20and%20size%20of%20the%20dividends%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bthe%20No.%201%20political%20issue%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Alaska.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20you're%20running%20as%20a%20Republican%2C%20an%20Independent%2C%20or%20a%20Democrat%20in%20the%20state%2C%20your%20political%20slogan%20will%20be%20your%20name%20and%20then%20'PFD%20defender'%20in%20large%20font%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20an%20Alaska%20resident%20who%20receives%20the%20permanent%20fund%20dividend%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-permanent-fund-basic-income%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724984882000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a25add93339b01f008b45d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-permanent-fund-basic-income%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Alaska%20Permanent%20Fund%2C%20which%20some%20compare%20to%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20helps%20reduce%20poverty.%20Residents%20got%20%241%2C312%20in%202023%3B%20here's%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-permanent-fund-basic-income%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hush%20money%20case%3A%20Trump%20seeks%20federal%20court%20intervention%20in%20bid%20to%20overturn%20conviction%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724984796000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112910742%2Cimgsize-90870.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhush-money-case-trump-seeks-federal-court-intervention-in-bid-to-overturn-conviction%2Farticleshow%2F112910209.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F112910209.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20has%20petitioned%20a%20federal%20court%20to%20step%20in%20on%20his%20hush%20money%20criminal%20case%2C%20aiming%20to%20reverse%20his%20con