r%20emergencies%2C%20and%20invest%20extra%20cash.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20director%20of%20investments%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbetterment-checking-cash-reserve-review%5C%22%3EBetterment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mindy%20Yu%C2%A0helps%20hundreds%20of%20people%20invest%20in%20the%20market%20wisely%20and%20grow%20their%20wealth.%20But%20Yu%20herself%20comes%20from%20humble%20beginnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20grew%20up%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York%2C%20in%20a%20Chinese%20immigrant%20family%20who%20lived%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%20Yu's%20father%20worked%20as%20a%20self-employed%20handyman%2C%20while%20her%20mother%20worked%20as%20a%20seamstress%20in%20Manhattan's%20Chinatown.%20Her%20mother%20eventually%20had%20to%20leave%20her%20job%20as%20Yu%20and%20her%20two%20siblings%20needed%20more%20support%20when%20they%20started%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20were%20definitely%20not%20office-type%20jobs%20with%20a%20steady%20paycheck.%20I%20have%20a%20brother%20and%20an%20older%20sister%2C%20so%20we%20saw%20the%20struggles%20my%20mom%20and%20dad%20had%20working%20hard%20to%20provide%20for%20our%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20Yu%20tells%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20time%20for%20Yu%20to%20go%20to%20college%2C%20she%20started%20exploring%20other%20industries%2C%20like%20fashion%20merchandising%2C%20before%20pursuing%20a%20career%20in%20finance.%20She%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BAfter%20I%20started%20understanding%20the%20power%20of%20investing%2C%20understanding%20how%20the%20finance%20industry%20can%20help%20people%20plan%2C%20save%2C%20and%20think%20about%20their%20financial%20futures%2C%20that%20was%20the%20lightbulb%20moment%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20experiences%20really%20transformed%20how%20I%20think%20about%20advice%20for%20clients%2C%20especially%20because%20you%20don't%20want%20them%20to%20fall%20into%20the%20same%20traps%20of%20being%20fearful%20and%20not%20investing%20correctly.%20That's%20always%20something%20that's%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20me%2C%20learning%20from%20my%20mistakes%20and%20making%20sure%20that%20our%20clients%20don't%20do%20the%20same%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20what%20financial%20advice%20she%20would%20give%20her%20parents%20if%20she%20could%20turn%20back%20time%2C%20Yu%20said%20she%20would%20tell%20them%20these%20three%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Focus%20on%20retirement%20planning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20so%20focused%20on%20us%20and%20helping%20three%20children%20get%20through%20college%2C%20they%20did%20not%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%3Eplanning%20for%20their%20own%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20can't%20only%20depend%20on%20Social%20Security%20benefits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%20parents%20didn't%20necessarily%20have%20access%20to%20traditional%20retirement%20accounts%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Yu%20wishes%20she%20had%20conversations%20with%20her%20parents%20about%20retirement%20planning%20earlier%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20not%20too%20late%20to%20start%20now%20and%20have%20those%20conversations%20with%20your%20parents.%20You%20can't%20take%20a%20loan%20out%20later%20in%20the%20future%20to%20maintain%20your%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20healthcare%20costs.%20Those%20are%20going%20to%20consistently%20rise%20year%20after%20year%2C%20and%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20burden.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Start%20an%20emergency%20fund%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20at%20least%20three%20to%20six%20months'%20worth%20of%20living%20expenses%2C%20which%20is%20typically%20kept%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20access%20in%20case%20of%20an%20emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20recognizes%20that%20her%20parents%20always%20wanted%20to%20save%20into%20an%20emergency%20fund%2C%20but%20that%20the%20odds%20were%20stacked%20against%20their%20family.%20She%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20difficult%20coming%20to%20this%20country%20without%20speaking%20English.%20That's%20hard%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20living.%20It's%20like%20being%20dropped%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere%20and%20not%20being%20able%20to%20communicate%2C%20which%20you%20need%20to%20try%20to%20survive%20and%20make%20a%20living.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20remembers%20that%20her%20family%20used%20to%20drive%20an%20older%20car%20while%20she%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20and%20sometimes%2C%20that%20car%20would%20break%20down%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20highway.%20If%20she%20could%20go%20back%20in%20time%2C%20Yu%20would%20explain%20to%20her%20parents%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20a%20dedicated%20emergency%20fund%20for%20those%20times%20when%20their%20car%20broke%20down%20on%20the%20highway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Invest%20any%20extra%20cash%20savings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20wishes%20her%20parents%20had%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-invest-in-stocks%5C%22%3Einvesting%20in%20the%20stock%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20parents%20were%20trying%20to%20save%20and%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20get%20adjusted%20here%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20and%20financial%20planning%20services%20are%20really%20expensive.%20No%20one%20would%20talk%20to%20you%20if%20you%20didn't%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20to%20work%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20language%20barrier%20also%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20Yu's%20parents%20to%20access%20basic%20personal%20finance%20skills%2C%20like%20investing%20and%20planning%20for%20retirement%2C%20that%20would%20have%20made%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20their%20family's%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYu%20adds%20that%20older%20generations%20within%20Asian%20American%20communities%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20conservative%20investors.%20She%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20community%20always%20focuses%20on%20saving%20dollar%20per%20dollar%2C%20instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20what%20that%20dollar%20looks%20like%20if%20you%20invested%20in%20the%20market.%20There's%20just%20not%20enough%20literacy%20and%20motivation%20for%20the%20older%20generation%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3ESoFi%20Invest%20is%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3Ebest%20robo-advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20investing%20options%20for%20low-cost%20automated%20or%20self-managed%20portfolios.%20Read%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsofi-invest-review%5C%22%3ESoFi%20investing%20review%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-american-investment-manager-advice-parents-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724969642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F627d8556dd983300191cc8b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%