0a%20crew%20member%20who%20survived%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fequipment%2Fb-1b-lancer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EB-1B%20Lancer%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20crash%20in%20South%20Dakota%20earlier%20this%20year%20said%20the%20official%20accident%20investigation%20report%20into%20the%20mishap%20wrongly%20criticized%20the%20airman's%20weight%20and%20unfairly%20put%20blame%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fbase-guide%2Fellsworth-air-force-base%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEllsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoni%20Smith%2C%20the%20mother-in-law%20of%20the%20instructor%20pilot%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20had%20submitted%20letters%20raising%20concerns%20about%20the%20incident%20to%20South%20Dakota%20Gov.%20Kristi%20Noem%2C%20as%20well%20as%20members%20of%20the%20state's%20delegation%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20criticism%20was%20that%20Smith%20said%20the%20report%20inaccurately%20highlighted%20the%20airman's%20alleged%20weight%20as%20being%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20260%26quot%3B%20pounds%2C%20which%20the%20report%20stated%20was%20over%20the%20245-pound%20maximum%2C%20something%20the%20investigator%20said%20%26quot%3Bfurther%20highlights%20the%20unit's%20degradation%20of%20culture%20and%20discipline.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESmith%20detailed%20in%20her%20letter%20and%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20her%20son-in-law%20never%20officially%20weighed%20more%20than%20245%20pounds%2C%20was%20never%20disqualified%20from%20flying%2C%20and%20passed%20his%20last%20physical%20fitness%20test%20just%20six%20weeks%20before%20the%20crash.%20She%20said%20that%20his%20alleged%20weight%20mentioned%20in%20the%20report%20was%20taken%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%2C%20which%20she%20called%20an%20inaccurate%20and%20unfair%20way%20to%20gather%20that%20data%2C%20especially%20as%20he%20was%20bandaged%20up%20and%20swollen%20from%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20medical%20professional%20at%20Monument%20Health%20stated%20that%20hospital%20bed%20weights%20are%20not%20accurate%20body%20measurements%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20weight%20was%20taken%20after%20the%20crash%20with%20a%20neck%20brace%2C%20boot%20brace%2C%20pelvic%20binder%2C%20legs%20binder%2C%20blanket%2C%20layers%20of%20bedding%20and%20pads%2C%20a%20remote%20for%20pain%20med%2C%20multiple%20IVs%2C%20multiple%20probes%20and%20cords%2C%20bandaging%20on%20three%20wounds%2C%20hospital%20gown%2C%20and%20blood%20pressure%20strap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20her%20son-in-law%20is%20still%20healing%20from%20serious%20back%20injuries%20as%20a%20result%20of%20ejecting%20from%20the%20B-1B%20Lancer%2C%20Smith%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20he%20could%20face%20disciplinary%20action%20due%20to%20his%20alleged%20weight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221207%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20charred%20remains%20of%20the%20B-1B%20Lancer%20after%20it%20crashed%20near%20the%20runway%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a2b777aab37011780aac14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22908%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20charred%20remains%20of%20the%20B-1B%20Lancer%20after%20it%20crashed%20near%20the%20runway%20of%20Ellsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20Aircraft%20Accident%20Investigation%20Board%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crash%20that%20Smith's%20son-in-law%20was%20injured%20in%20happened%20on%20January%204%20at%20Ellsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20South%20Dakota.%20The%20B-1B%20Lancer%2C%20valued%20at%20%24450%20million%2C%20was%20on%20a%20training%20exercise%20with%20four%20crew%20members%20aboard.%20The%20bomber%20crashed%20roughly%20100%20feet%20short%20of%20the%20runway%2C%20skidded%20more%20than%205%2C000%20feet%20down%20the%20tarmac%2C%20and%20then%20caught%20on%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20four%20crew%20members%20safely%20ejected%3B%20Smith's%20son-in-law%20suffered%20multiple%20fractures%20and%20severely%20injured%20his%20spine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECol.%20Erick%20Lord%2C%20the%20Accident%20Investigation%20Board%20president%2C%20issued%20a%20scathing%20report%20that%20was%20publicized%20late%20last%20month.%20The%20report%20pointed%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfailure%20to%20perform%20standard%20crew%20resource%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20along%20with%20adverse%20weather%20conditions%2C%20ineffective%20flying%20operations%20supervision%2C%20lack%20of%20awareness%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Ban%20unhealthy%20organizational%20culture%20that%20permitted%20degradation%20of%20airmanship%20skills%26quot%3B%20as%20contributing%20factors%20in%20the%20crash%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F07%2F25%2Freport-unhealthy-culture-ellsworth-air-force-base-units-contributed-b-1b-lancer-crash.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20first%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELord%20also%20singled%20out%20the%20instructor%20pilot's%20weight%2C%20saying%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20review%20of%20the%20post-mishap%20medical%20treatment%20records%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20%5Binstructor%20pilot%5D%20exceeded%20the%20maximum%20weight%20limit%20of%20the%20ACES%20II%20ejection%20seat%20(211%20lbs.)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fair-force%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAir%20Force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E-adjusted%20maximum%20weight%20limit%20(245%20lbs.)%20for%20safe%20and%20effective%20use.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20claims%20the%20instructor%20pilot%20was%20just%20under%20the%20245-pound%20weight%20limit%20before%20the%20mishap%20and%20states%20that%20the%20post-mishap%20report%20of%20nearly%20260%20pounds%20weight%20%26quot%3Blikely%20contributed%20to%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20injuries%20noted%20from%20the%20mishap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aircrew%20member%20directs%20a%20B-1B%20Lancer%20onto%20the%20runway%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a2b11e1a227600e631be72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aircrew%20member%20directs%20a%20B-1B%20Lancer%20onto%20the%20runway%20at%20Ellsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20South%20Dakota.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Airman%201st%20Class%20Dylan%20Maher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20Global%20Strike%20Command%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20many%20of%20the%20specific%20claims%20in%20Smith's%20letter%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailed%20but%20said%20the%20organization%20was%20taking%20action%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20report's%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20AIB%20report%20details%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20mishap%2C%20crew%20landing%20short%20of%20the%20runway%2C%20and%20additional%20factors%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20accident%2C%26quot%3B%20Air%20Force%20Global%20Strike%20Command%20spokesman%20Lt.%20Col.%20John%20Severns%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%2028th%20Bomb%20Wing%20has%20been%20working%20to%20address%20those%20factors%2C%20plus%20taking%20appropriate%20administrative%20actions.%20The%20Air%20Force%20does%20not%20discuss%20the%20results%20of%20those%20types%20of%20action%20as%20they%20are%20protected%20by%20the%20Privacy%20Act.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoughly%20a%20week%20after%20the%20findings%20became%20public%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20the%2028th%20Operations%20Group%20was%20fired%20from%20his%20role%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20trust%20and%20confidence%20in%20his%20ability%20to%20command%2C%20based%20on%20the%20findings%20of%20an%20Accident%20Investigation%20Board%20report%20into%20the%20January%204%20crash%20of%20a%20B-1B%20bomber%20at%20Ellsworth%2C%26quot%3B%20Air%20Force%20Global%20Strike%20Command%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELord%20took%20aim%20at%20the%2028th%20Operational%20Support%20Squadron%20and%20the%2034th%20Bomb%20Squadron%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20under%20the%2028th%20Operations%20Group%20commander's%20leadership%2C%20in%20the%20report%2C%20saying%20%26quot%3Bthe%20lack%20of%20effective%20flying%20operations%20supervision%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bfailure%20to%20communicate%20airfield%20and%20weather%20capabilities%20and%20conditions%20all%20speak%20to%20culture%20and%20leadership%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20marked%20the%20first%20time%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20that%20a%20B-1B%20Lancer%20had%20crashed.%20The%20previous%20crash%20occurred%20in%20August%202013%2C%20when%20a%20bomber%20flying%20out%20of%20Ellsworth%20went%20down%20near%20Broadus%2C%20Montana%2C%20causing%20fire%20damage%20to%20private%20property%20and%20destroying%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20explained%20that%20the%20recent%20crash%20was%20already%20a%20lot%20for%20the%20crew%20to%20grapple%20with%2C%20but%20the%20subsequent%20report%20by%20Lord%20caused%20even%20more%20stress%20and%20worries%20for%20the%20airmen%20and%20others%20at%20the%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225870%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22B-1B%20Lancers%20from%20Dyess%20and%20Ellsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20South%20Dakota%2C%20sit%20on%20the%20flightline%20at%20Dyess%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Texas%2C%20Feb.%201%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c62e3b6fcb546d2d4dd951%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223906%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EB-1B%20Lancers%20from%20Dyess%20and%20Ellsworth%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20South%20Dakota%2C%20sit%20on%20the%20flightline%20at%20Dyess%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Texas%2C%20Feb.%201%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Leon%20Redfern%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mother-in-law%20of%20the%20crew%20member%20also%20took%20aim%20at%20other%20specifics%20in%20the%20report%2C%20claiming%20that%20icing%20and%20wind%20shear%20played%20larger%20roles%20in%20the%20crash%20than%20stated%20in%20the%20findings%2C%20and%20she%20said%20that%20Lord's%20%26quot%3Bcomments%20are%20seething%20with%20hatred%20and%20disrespect%20to%20the%20outstanding%20aviators%20of%20the%2034th%20Bomb%20Squadron.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAviators%20and%20crew%20members%20who%20have%20served%20at%20Ellsworth%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20base%20culture%2C%20said%20the%20report%20harmed%20morale%20and%20made%20them%20feel%20like%20they%20weren't%20dedicated%20to%20their%20jobs%2C%20especially%20when%20members%20of%20the%20B-1B%20Lancer%20community%20say%20they're%20already%20doing%20more%20with%20fewer%20people%2C%20airplanes%2C%20and%20resources%20compared%20to%20other%20airframes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20a%20hit%20like%20this%20comes%20in%2C%20it%20does%20real%20damage%20to%20morale%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20aviator%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20gave%20the%20impression%20that%20one%20mistake%20occurs%20and%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20hung%20out%20to%20dry%2C%20and%20the%20root%20cause%20for%20that%20mistake%20being%20made%20wasn't%20a%20culture%20of%20wanton%20disregard%20for%20regu